{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 06:09:50.786740", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope and topology\n- Fabric: multi-tier Clos (fat-tree) with EBGP everywhere: super-spine (AS 65000) ↔ spines (AS 65100/65101) ↔ leaves (AS 65200/65201) ↔ hosts.\n- Devices examined: super_spine_router_0, spine_router_0_0, spine_router_0_1, leaf_router_0_0, leaf_router_0_1, and hosts pc_0_0, pc_0_1.\n\nTests and data collected\n- End-to-end reachability tests (multi-host subset) and direct ping pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1.\n- BGP status on all routers: show bgp ipv4 unicast summary.\n- FRR running configuration on leaves.\n- IP routing tables on all routers.\n\nSummary assessment\n- Data-plane: Healthy. All sampled inter-host pings succeeded with 0% loss and low RTTs. Direct host-to-host (pc_0_0 → pc_0_1) also succeeded (0% loss, ~2.7 ms avg).\n- Control-plane: Healthy. All EBGP sessions on leaves, spines, and the super-spine are Established; routing tables contain the expected /24 leaf networks, and ECMP is present where expected on the spines.\n\nDetailed findings\n1) Reachability\n- Multi-host reachability sampling shows 0% packet loss across tested flows with RTTs in the low single-digit milliseconds typical of a lab fabric.\n- pc_0_0 → pc_0_1: 4/4 received, 0% loss, rtt avg 2.656 ms.\n\n2) BGP neighbor health\n- leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200): 8 peers Established; State/PfxRcd per peer ~31; advertising 10.0.0.0/24 per config.\n- leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201): 8 peers Established; State/PfxRcd per peer ~31; advertising 10.0.1.0/24 per config.\n- spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100): 12 peers Established (4 super-spine peers + multiple leaves); State/PfxRcd ranges 1–32 depending on neighbor.\n- spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101): 12 peers Established; State/PfxRcd commonly 29–32 from leaf neighbors; 32 from super-spine peers.\n- super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000): 32 peers Established; receiving and sending prefixes to all connected spines (e.g., PfxSnt 32).\n\n3) Routing tables\n- Leaves:\n  - Directly connected /24 present for local host networks (C>* 10.0.0.0/24 on leaf_router_0_0, C>* 10.0.1.0/24 on leaf_router_0_1).\n  - BGP-learned routes for all other 10.<pod>.<leaf>.0/24 networks present; next-hops point to pod spines (e.g., via 172.16.1.0 and 172.16.1.16).\n- Spines:\n  - Learn local-pod leaf /24s from the leaves.\n  - For remote-pod /24s, ECMP entries via the super-spine sessions are visible (one “>” best plus additional “*” eligible next-hops).\n- Super-spine:\n  - Has BGP-learned routes for the fabric’s /24s, with neighbors in all spine ASNs established.\n\nObserved irregularities (not service-impacting)\n- Prefix count asymmetry on spine_router_0_0 vs spine_router_0_1 from super-spine peers:\n  - spine_router_0_0: State/PfxRcd ~24 per super-spine neighbor.\n  - spine_router_0_1: State/PfxRcd ~32 per super-spine neighbor.\n  - Despite this, both spines’ routing tables show broad coverage of 10.x/24 networks and forwarding is correct. This likely reflects differences in best-path acceptance per session (e.g., AS-path/MED tie-breaks or per-neighbor advertisement differences) rather than missing reachability.\n- Leaves appear to peer with a larger set of spines (8 peers) than the simplified topology description (2 spines). This indicates the lab is a larger Clos instance; behavior remains consistent with EBGP fabric operation.\n\nAnomaly detection\n- No data-plane anomalies detected (no loss, normal RTTs).\n- No control-plane faults detected: all BGP adjacencies are Established, and expected routes exist end-to-end.\n- Minor control-plane observation: differing per-neighbor prefix counts (as above) without impact.\n\nLocalization\n- No faulty devices identified. All examined routers and hosts exhibit normal behavior and correct routing.\n\nLikely root cause (for the minor observation)\n- The per-neighbor PfxRcd disparity is most likely due to normal EBGP best-path selection and/or per-neighbor advertisement differences within the larger lab fabric (e.g., some prefixes preferred via other super-spine sessions), resulting in different accepted-prefix counts per session but full overall coverage. There is no evidence of filtering or session flaps impacting connectivity.\n\nConclusion\n- The network is operating normally. Control-plane convergence is complete, and data-plane connectivity between leaves (including pc_0_0 and pc_0_1) is healthy. No actionable anomalies were found.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 23107, "output_tokens": 5840, "total_tokens": 28947, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 22784}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 4672}}}
